data.title: 'Ramsay family definitely complete': Gordon Ramsay and Wife Tana welcome sixth baby

data.text:
Synopsis

The couple, already parents to five children, including Megan, Jack, Holly, Tilly, and Oscar, shared heartwarming photos capturing the family's happiness. Tana Ramsay, in her Instagram post, described the past nine months as nerve-wracking and expressed gratitude for the blessing of their complete family. She wrote, "Ramsay family definitely complete. Jesse James Ramsay, we love you so much."

Gordon Ramsay and his wife Tana Ramsay on Saturday welcomed their sixth baby, a son named Jesse James Ramsay. The celebrity chef, who recently celebrated his birthday, shared the news on Instagram. Ramsay expressed his excitement and said, "One more bundle of love to the Ramsay brigade!! 3 boys, 3 girls…. Done."

The couple, already parents to five children, including Megan, Jack, Holly, Tilly, and Oscar, shared heartwarming photos capturing the family's happiness. Tana Ramsay, in her Instagram post, described the past nine months as nerve-wracking and expressed gratitude for the blessing of their complete family. She wrote, "Ramsay family definitely complete. Jesse James Ramsay, we love you so much."

Gordon Ramsay, previously discussing the possibility of expanding their family, humorously mentioned Tana's desire for "another one." He joked about being a part of school sports day celebrations with a walker, saying, "I’m going to be at school celebrating sports day with a f---ing walker!” the chef said, laughing. "'Hey, who's your granddad?' 'That's my dad, actually.' "

Tana Ramsay has also expressed a desire for a big family, "I'm one of four, Gordon's one of four, so it's sort of second nature to me," she told People in an interview.
